SoyiSambu Mitua MCA Stephen Wamalwa has unearthed a corruption syndicate at the Bungoma County Assembly that involves senior officials making non-existent payments to particular contractors and suppliers and thereafter sharing the loot. He pointed out a case where the assembly paid a hotel in Kisumu Sh510,000 allegedly in December 2017 for a seminar that MCAS never attended “We have documents showing that 25 MCAS attended a workshop of the agriculture committee which I am member yet we didn’t and the hotel was paid,” said wamalwa. He is now calling on the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commussion to investigate. Click here for the latest political news